# Trinity Relit Project

Browser-based text adventure faithfully reproducing Infocom's Trinity (1986) with bilingual English/Chinese text.

## Key Files

- `prototype/js/engine.js` — GameState + GameEngine classes (DO NOT modify without explicit request)
- `prototype/js/data/*.js` — Chapter data (rooms, events). Follow `prototype/CHAPTER_RULES.md`
- `prototype/js/data/items.js` — All game items
- `prototype/js/parser.js` — Input parser
- `prototype/js/embedding.js` — Semantic matching via Web Worker
- `zparse.py` — Z-machine parser for extracting data from `Trinity 1986/TRINITY.DAT`

## Core Principle

ALL English text must come from the original 1986 Infocom game. Never create original English content. Map structure must match Z-machine data extracted by `zparse.py`.

## Z-machine Direction Properties

63=N, 62=NE, 61=E, 60=SE, 59=S, 58=SW, 57=W, 56=NW, 55=UP, 54=DOWN, 53=IN, 52=OUT.
2-byte value = room object number. 3+ bytes = conditional routine.

## When Writing Chapters

1. First read `prototype/CHAPTER_PLAN.md` to find the target chapter's room list, mechanics, and subtasks
2. Then follow `prototype/CHAPTER_RULES.md` for the complete workflow, API reference, and validation checklist
3. Use `prototype/js/data/prologue.js` as the reference implementation
